        "speaker": "Chandra Janakiraman",
        "timestamp": "00:00:00",
        "quote": "I started noticing that there was a certain mystique and aura about product strategy. There was this perception that some people were intrinsically really good at strategy and others were not. It was almost as if there was a strategy gene you needed to be born with to be good at it.",
