        "speaker": "And so we're like, of course. And I turn to him and I'm like, \"I'm Jonathan. I run a 10 person agency out of Vancouver.\" And he says, \"Hey, I'm Garrett Camp. I started a company called Uber.\" And so ironically, I meet the founder of Uber, the company that is in the process of disrupting the entire taxi industry worldwide in the back of a taxi cab. And what happened next basically changed my career forever. We end up at this party. At the time I was spamming Uber's referral program. Kind of a long story, but essentially I was using paid search to camp out on their branded keywords. And as people would sign up with my confusingly similar snippet to Uber's organic snippet, I was essentially siphoning off referral credits. So I would get $20 every single time someone signed up.",
